            Mars InSight: Inside Nasa's mission control
            After a journey of more than 6 months, Nasaâ€™s InSight Lander will make an attempt to land on the surface of the Red Planet. In the final few minutes of its journey, the spacecraft will have to decelerate - from six times the speed of a bullet - enough to make a safe touchdown on the surface. Our science correspondent Victoria Gill has been to the centre of operations and found out about an unusual tradition.
                
